<BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James           
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B48C005.htm'>Galatians 5</A></P><CENTER><H2             
ALIGN=CENTER>The Epistle of Paul to the Galatians</H2></CENTER><P><A            
HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5  
WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 6</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>Brethren, if a man be overtaken in  
a fault, ye which are spiritual, restore such an one in the spirit of meekness; 
considering thyself, lest thou also be tempted.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>
<A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Bear ye one another's burdens, and so fulfil   
the law of MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD>
<TD><P>For if a man think himself to be something, when he is nothing, he       
deceiveth himself.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>But let every man prove his own work, and then shall he have rejoicing   
in himself alone, and not in another.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>For every man shall bear his own burden.</P></TD> 
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Let him that is taught 
in the word communicate unto him that teacheth in all good things.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>Be not deceived; ELOHIYM is 
not mocked: for whatsoever a man soweth, that shall he also reap.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>For he that soweth to his   
flesh shall of the flesh reap corruption; but he that soweth to the Spirit      
shall of the Spirit reap life everlasting.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>And let us not be weary in well doing: for in due 
season we shall reap, if we faint not.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>As we have therefore opportunity, let us do     
good unto all men, especially unto them who are of the household of faith.</P>  
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>Ye see how      
large a letter I have written unto you with mine own hand.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>As many as desire to make a fair  
shew in the flesh, they constrain you to be circumcised; only lest they should  
suffer persecution for the cross of MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>For neither they themselves who are          
circumcised keep the law; but desire to have you circumcised, that they may     
glory in your flesh.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4>    
</TD><TD><P>But forbid that I should glory, save in the cross of our ADONAY     
YAHSHUA MASHIYACH, by whom the world is crucified unto me, and I unto the       
world.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>For   
in MASHIYACH YAHSHUA neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor               
uncircumcision, but a new creature.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16>
<H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>And as many as walk according to this rule, peace be on  
them, and mercy, and upon the Israel of ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD           
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>From henceforth let no man        
trouble me: for I bear in my body the marks of the ADONAY YAHSHUA.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>Brethren, the grace of    
our ADONAY YAHSHUA MASHIYACH be with your spirit. Amen.</P></TD></TR></TABLE>   
